<br>


'''''Level 37.5''''' is the 5''th'' sublevel of [[Level 37]].

<br><div style="background-color:rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1); color: white; margin:1em;font-family:Jost; padding:5px 10px; text-align:center;"><font size="6">'''''Description:'''''</font></div>
----
<div style="font-family:Jost">'''''Level 37.5,''''' commonly referred to by wanderers as '''«Mist Procedure''»''''', resembles a vast, sprawling network, stretching endlessly in all directions, and mainly comprised of interconnected rooms and corridors, similar to traditional eastern saunas – hammams. Contrary to the main level, the interior seems never to grow in size or show any other signs of deformation, being almost identical to each other in every area. The walls, ceilings, and floors of the level usually appear to be constructed from ceramic tiles, though varying, because of their belonging to a state change, which mainly affects the structure of passages and, as said before, the material they are built with. This, however, never seems to destroy or deform rooms located inside the level, relating to the properties of tiles, making them the most stable and safe areas for the potential wanderer.
{{Blurimage|file=Hamam4.jpg|hovertext=The Stairs|caption='''''Artistic interpretation of a typical hammam room, found inside the level.'''''}}
While traversing within the boundaries of winding hammams, one will, although rarely, find small but unusually deep pits, filled to the top with cold, ultrapure water. The holes seem to function as pools, although they are too deep to accommodate wanderers. Their maximum depth seems to vary, typically reaching about 50-60 meters, and in some cases extending indefinitely below, without any confirmed bottom. Those who submerge in them, however, for unknown reasons, never feel the coldness of water, instead being in a state of trance and relaxation, similar to that of Level 37’s effect, but on a much larger scale. Discovered traces of magnesium sulfate (Epsom salt) and an anomalous component from the aforementioned level, most likely not involved in this condition, because of their weakened effect on this level. Although it is not recommended to stay in the cold water for prolonged periods of time because of possible risks regarding potential frostbite that can affect the wanderer’s body if staying long enough in the pools. It is advised to avoid any attempts of diving procedures due to their danger without the equipment of additional lights, as their depths lack any light sources, which could easily lead to lethal drownings.

Ceiling lights shine brightly with hot, orange light, illuminating the countless passages with blurred, remarkable light and evoking feelings of potential nostalgia in one’s relaxed mind. These sources seem to increase the effect provided by cold pools, by giving wanderers, as said in their reports, a state of mild delight. Dimmed shadows cast upon ceramic walls at slightly irregular angles, leaving some small areas completely darkened, as no windows exist within the boundaries of '''''Level 37.5'''''.

A distant, mist-like substance flies through countless interior rooms, covering them in constant, never-changing patterns of thick, viscous air, filled with the same ultrapure water, with a lukewarm temperature, instead of the usual bone-chilling coldness. Its lukewarmness, compared with the general abundance of this substance across the level, can suggest its possible origins – vents, rarely found on the floor in the rooms. Although it is impossible to completely ensure this statement, because of mist invisibility in the forming stage.

Sound variation, nonetheless, has been confirmed to behave normally within the bounds of '''''Level 37.5''''', serving as depicted, contrary to the main level. All of their properties seem to never differentiate from those of normal soundwaves, with the only exception being slight '''«muffling»''' created by the aforementioned mist.
{{Blurimage|file=Sauna1.jpg|hovertext=The Stairs|caption='''''Image of a wooden room inside of Level 37.5.'''''}}
Rarely, dead ends could be found, serving as a restriction to the exploration of interconnected rooms, if the wanderer decides not to go back. These dead ends seem to manifest in form of closed rooms with the openable set of sliding glass doors, cutting them off from the regular areas. The interior of these rooms represents wooden saunas, distinguishing themselves from normal hammam aesthetics. However, due to the leakage of a meaningful amount of steam to them, many the of wooden rooms, as they were called by wanderers, have been molded, making entrance to them not recommended, leading to potentially dangerous situations.

Overgrowth flora is seen to commonly appear in these areas, surrounding the walls, and, in rare cases, the entire interior space of them, making traversing through the wooden rooms difficult, as breaching plants presented within the aforementioned rooms is considered among wanderers, mostly impossible with usual equipment. The visual structure of flora specimens varies, but always tends to stay within the boundaries of what are considered herbal plants. Most of the time, they are encountered in the form of vines, existing or similar to the counterparts located in the '''Frontrooms'''.<br><div style="background-color:rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1); color: white; margin:1em;font-family:Jost; padding:5px 10px; text-align:center;"><font size="6">'''''Bases, outposts and settlements:'''''</font></div>
----
''Because of a lack of resources compared with the small amount of useful exits, it is believed impossible to create such established communities within the boundaries of sublevel.''

<br><div style="background-color:rgba(255, 255, 255, 0); color: white; margin:1em;font-family:Jost; padding:5px 10px; text-align:center;"><font size="6">'''''Attached Logs:'''''</font></div>
----
''The following is what is usually assumed to be the first mention of this sub-level amongst wanderers, serving as a significant benefit to level discovery history, since its inclusion in this document:''
<div class="titleblock"><span class="titlebox" style="color: white;">Recovered Note:</span><br><center>''Misty fate:''</center>''After traveling through what felt like an endless myriad of dimensions, I found what seemed initially to be a safe haven at first - '''Poolrooms''', the dimension of water serenity. I spent many weeks there, tirelessly enjoying the peace it brought me while bathing in countless pools.''
{{Blurimage|file=Hammam.png|hovertext=Halls|caption=Quiet dead end.}}
''Eventually, I started losing joy in it, thinking about its hopelessness and emptiness, which I had never thought of beforehand. '''"What could possibly go wrong?"''' - my mind said in confusion. '''"Maybe this place can't accept me?"''' - I continued. I looked down at my body, terrified by its rustiness and moldiness, and understood why my enjoyment had faded. "I spend too much time in there, I need to wash myself". After I washed myself, I unexpectedly ended up in a strange place. As any sane person would, my hands searched for any mentions of this level inside the M.E.G. Database, only to be greeted by confusion, as I realized my new discovery. ''Strange Spa complex, comprised of endless hammams, with its textures being similar to Poolrooms tiles, sickly reminding me of past experience. Soon enough, a deep pool shone before my eyes, filled to the brim with crystal-pure water. I jumped in it, meeting what seemed an endless delight to me. After swimming in it for a long time, I realized my mistake when my body started feeling too cold for the warm surroundings. I needed to search for exits... I don't remember much since then, but one thing that caught my memory in place was vine-like plants, with wooden walls, some rooms, and sudden Nocliping that got me to my current location, to [[Level 416|'''Level 416''']].
</div>
<br><div style="background-color:rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.1); color: white; margin:1em;font-family:Jost; padding:5px 10px; text-align:center;"><font size="6">'''''Entrances and exits:'''''</font></div>
----

<br><div style="background-color:rgba(255, 255, 255, 0); color: white; margin:1em;font-family:Jost; padding:5px 10px; text-align:center;"><font size="5">'''''Entrances:'''''</font></div>
* To enter this level, one may venture inside the '''Terminus''' part of [[Level 30|'''''Level 30''''']] to find abandoned hammam within it. Once wanderer exits it, they will appear inside Level 37.5.
* If wanderer is currently taking a hygienic procedure inside the pools of [[Level 37|'''''Level 37''''']], after completing it, they will most likely end up within this level.
* Immersing inside the '''Guts''' part of [[Level 989|'''''Level 989''''']] has small chance to take wanderer to this level.
* A doorframe filled with water in [[Level 7.5]] will lead one here.

<br><div style="background-color:rgba(255, 255, 255, 0); color: white; margin:1em;font-family:Jost; padding:5px 10px; text-align:center;"><font size="5">'''''Exits:'''''</font></div>

* While swimming to the bottom of cold-watered pools, wanderer has the potential opportunity to find ice inside it, if they noclip through them, they will appear in Level [[Level 202|'''''Level 202''''']].
* Nocliping through wooden rooms inside the level has chance taking one to [[Level 416|'''''Level 416''''']].</font></div>{{Redirect|Prev=37.3|Next=37.6}}
